innerHTML: Completely redid the code just for a new GUI. Biggest time waste in my life. Took me over one week. I'm exhausted. The full changelog wouldn't fit in here. Just look at this ridiculous git commit.
Inserted some data for the Longfin Approach Vehicle Prep. Also added all the data for The Cluckin' Bell Farm Raid.

Obsoleted the speedrun.com/gtao map for Cayo Perico, by adding all their features. This includes the newly added Weapon Loadout mission markers and the Kosatka Approach Vehicle spawns. I will be working on adding the rest of the actual preps over the next few days.
Reformatted a bunch of code, added Cayo Perico Heist Prep locations: Cutting Torch, Fingerprint Cloner, Plasma Cutter.
Added all the images for LD Organics Products with the combined work of three people (myself, Pelloh and EditChris)
Added some Cayo Perico related locations. Will add more at a later date.
Added a few images. Nothing interesting. Also added opengraph tags.
Added LD Organics Products to the website, finally completing the major collectibles.
Added Signal Jammers to the website.
Added a bunch of timers: Casino Wheel Spin, Chips Buy Cooldown and VIP Registration.
The title of the marker you clicked on will now be highlighted, to avoid confusion.
Now all Playing Cards have datapoints, icons and they're listed. Also made a way to give different markers in the same set different icons.
All movie props now have proper data points. Also finally decided on a release scheme: bigUpdate.smallUpdate.minorFix.
Started work on Movie Props - all the ones with a fixed location now show up on the map.
Data now stores the preferences for showing counties.
Data can now be saved and moved around! Also, data will be formatted appropriately.

You can now mark collectibles as completed; the `Show All`, `Hide All`, `Show Completed` and `Hide Completed` buttons now work properly. The Youtube video player has now been fixed of a bug where it wouldn't go to the proper timestamp.
The Cayo Perico Heist and the Casino Heist now have timers in the `Tools` section.

Now the map saves the last tile selection, alongside the last zoom and coordinate you were looking at, so that refreshing the page doesn't zoom you out completely. Also having a link that points to something in the GUI will open it on load.
Added tile selection to map, now able to switch between `game`, `render` and `print`.
Made the map work, aligned the SVGs kindly <del>stolen from</del> provided by GTALens.com. Manually got all the datapoints for Action Figures and descriptions.
